WEBVTT

00:06.966 --> 00:08.634
- Previously on Reacher...
- Little Wing can knock

00:08.718 --> 00:10.594
anything out of the sky.

00:10.678 --> 00:12.430
- Azhari Mahmoud.
- Yeah, we've been
calling him A.M.

00:12.513 --> 00:13.889
His only God is money.

00:13.973 --> 00:15.558
[Reacher] This buy was supposed
to happen with bearer bonds.

00:15.641 --> 00:18.144
You can carry an untraceable
fortune in a briefcase.

00:18.227 --> 00:20.020
Tony Swan's alive.
Swan personally

00:20.104 --> 00:22.356
signed off on the shipment;
it's a digital thumbprint.

00:22.440 --> 00:23.524
I'm not gonna assume
Swan's dirty.

00:23.607 --> 00:25.651
In an investigation,
assumptions kill.

00:25.735 --> 00:28.988
- Malcolm Lavoy.
- If anyone knew you were
involved, you'd be indicted.

00:29.071 --> 00:30.573
Get rid of the bad guys,
keep my hands clean.

00:30.656 --> 00:32.616
- We call that a win-win.
- [Marlo] Someone in engineering

00:32.700 --> 00:34.243
had manipulated
the testing board

00:34.326 --> 00:35.953
to randomly flag
operational chips

00:36.036 --> 00:38.038
- as defective.
- The Little Wing chips
will be ready

00:38.122 --> 00:39.957
to install in the missiles
by the time you get here.

00:40.040 --> 00:41.834
- Perfect.
- [Reacher] We need
to know exactly

00:41.917 --> 00:44.545
where the missiles are headed,
so we can intercept them.

00:44.628 --> 00:46.589
- [grunts]
- [screams]

00:46.672 --> 00:48.716
- What do you want?
- You and your buddy
come here now.

00:48.799 --> 00:50.843
My cohort's name is Neagley,
and she's dead.

00:50.926 --> 00:52.970
Your private security,
former Seals and Rangers,

00:53.053 --> 00:55.097
- I need 'em.
- [Lavoy] Done.
- Hey. Beat it.

00:55.181 --> 00:56.182
[grunts]

00:56.265 --> 00:57.767
- [laughs]
- That kid just gave me an idea.

00:57.850 --> 00:59.393
What, you're just gonna
walk in there?

00:59.477 --> 01:00.853
[Reacher] Don't worry,
I'm not just gonna

01:00.936 --> 01:02.271
lie down and take it.

01:02.354 --> 01:03.272
[buzzer sounds]

01:03.355 --> 01:04.648
- [Pierce] Hands up.
- [grunts]

01:07.401 --> 01:09.403
♪ ♪

01:25.002 --> 01:26.962
[Pierce] Stop.

01:36.388 --> 01:38.516
[Langston laughing] Fuck.

01:38.599 --> 01:41.185
Surveillance photos
don't do you justice.

01:47.066 --> 01:50.319
You're gonna make a hell of
a hole when you hit the ground.

01:53.656 --> 01:55.491
A hell of a hole.

01:56.534 --> 01:58.536
[phone ringing]

02:04.041 --> 02:05.709
Get him ready.

02:06.710 --> 02:09.088
Yeah, what did you find out?

02:10.798 --> 02:12.091
Climb on.

02:13.133 --> 02:14.260
No.

02:17.596 --> 02:19.807
No?

02:19.890 --> 02:21.642
You aren't in charge here...
[grunts]

02:21.725 --> 02:24.353
- [grunting]
- [shouting]

02:39.159 --> 02:40.327
Where is she?

02:41.412 --> 02:43.873
Must've got a call from
one of your pals on the force.

02:43.956 --> 02:45.708
There's only one body
down at the coroner's office,

02:45.791 --> 02:48.460
and it ain't Neagley.
Now, where is she?

02:48.544 --> 02:50.337
Put the gun down.

02:50.421 --> 02:53.132
We both know you can't shoot me
till you find her.

02:53.215 --> 02:55.301
She's your last loose end.

02:57.344 --> 02:58.888
You're right.

02:58.971 --> 03:00.723
I can't shoot you.

03:00.806 --> 03:01.849
[screams]

03:01.932 --> 03:03.183
Fuck.

03:03.267 --> 03:05.019
[coughs, whimpers]

03:06.270 --> 03:08.689
Sit down. We're gonna talk.

03:14.612 --> 03:16.447
I don't want
to leave anything

03:16.530 --> 03:18.782
for ballistics.
Dig that slug out of him.

03:18.866 --> 03:21.076
We got 'em right
where we want 'em, boss.

03:24.622 --> 03:26.874
[shouting]

03:26.957 --> 03:28.959
[grunting]

03:31.545 --> 03:33.547
[thunder crashing]

03:44.558 --> 03:46.560
♪ ♪

03:58.238 --> 03:59.865
[exhales]

04:04.536 --> 04:05.871
One.

04:08.540 --> 04:10.918
Two.

04:11.001 --> 04:13.462
One.

04:13.545 --> 04:15.756
Two.

04:15.839 --> 04:17.841
One.

04:17.925 --> 04:19.134
Two.

04:20.719 --> 04:22.721
[breathing heavily]

04:25.975 --> 04:28.060
[line ringing]

04:28.143 --> 04:30.062
Perimeter guards neutralized.
What's your ETA?

04:30.145 --> 04:31.730
[Seaver] Three minutes out.

04:31.814 --> 04:33.816
Copy that.
[breathing heavily]

04:35.401 --> 04:37.111
[yells]

04:37.194 --> 04:38.654
Oh, God.

04:38.737 --> 04:40.489
I had this whole thing
planned out.

04:40.572 --> 04:42.950
We get paid,

04:43.033 --> 04:44.660
let some time go by,

04:44.743 --> 04:46.286
and then quietly retire.

04:46.370 --> 04:50.207
But then your boy Swan
starts sniffing around.

04:50.290 --> 04:52.292
He brought his pals in on it,

04:52.376 --> 04:54.503
and fucked

04:54.586 --> 04:57.381
my well-thought-out plan

04:57.464 --> 04:59.883
like a Times Square

04:59.967 --> 05:01.218
whore!

05:03.387 --> 05:05.305
[panting]

05:05.389 --> 05:07.224
But that's okay,
'cause now we use Swan

05:07.307 --> 05:08.684
to sign off on our paperwork.

05:08.767 --> 05:10.978
If anybody else comes
poking around,

05:11.061 --> 05:13.480
it looks like he did the deal,
took the money and ran.

05:13.564 --> 05:15.607
And I still end up
with my toes in the sand

05:15.691 --> 05:18.110
and a bronze ass on my lap.

05:18.193 --> 05:20.362
But now that plan has
gone to shit, too,

05:20.446 --> 05:22.156
'cause I got one of you
fucking assholes

05:22.239 --> 05:23.949
running around out there.

05:24.033 --> 05:25.743
Where is she?!

05:25.826 --> 05:27.828
[panting]

05:29.496 --> 05:31.123
You seem upset.

05:31.206 --> 05:33.459
You're too stubborn
for your own fucking good.

05:34.877 --> 05:36.879
Just like the men
you used to command.

05:38.213 --> 05:40.257
I offered to cut Swan in.

05:40.340 --> 05:43.218
- Where is he?
- [Langston] Your buddy?

05:43.302 --> 05:44.470
He's here.

05:46.138 --> 05:47.598
You want to see him?

05:47.681 --> 05:49.475
♪ ♪

06:02.112 --> 06:05.407
See, I didn't need
all of him to frame him.

06:07.117 --> 06:08.243
Just his fingerprint

06:08.327 --> 06:10.829
to get into the computer,

06:10.913 --> 06:12.998
sign off on some documents,

06:13.082 --> 06:16.168
and his iris to scan

06:16.251 --> 06:19.713
when he logged in and out of
certain parts of the building.

06:19.797 --> 06:22.841
And a pristine house...

06:22.925 --> 06:25.886
It looked like he took
the money and ran,

06:25.969 --> 06:28.347
even leaving
his poor dog behind.

06:30.766 --> 06:32.184
[scoffs]

06:38.273 --> 06:40.067
Had to be a hero.

06:40.150 --> 06:41.652
Did you teach him that?

06:41.735 --> 06:43.445
Is this your fault?

06:49.118 --> 06:50.536
This reunion's over.

06:50.619 --> 06:51.912
I got a meeting with a man
that's gonna

06:51.995 --> 06:53.455
give me $65 million.

06:53.539 --> 06:55.290
Load those two on a chopper,

06:55.374 --> 06:57.668
and then come back
for this asshole.

07:08.720 --> 07:10.264
No matter what I do to you,

07:10.347 --> 07:12.224
you're not gonna tell me
where Neagley is, are you?

07:14.601 --> 07:17.938
Yeah... piece of shit.

07:19.857 --> 07:21.859
♪ ♪

07:38.959 --> 07:40.502
[Neagley] You came through,
Lavoy.

07:40.586 --> 07:42.421
Sweet.

07:54.641 --> 07:56.894
Fuck.

08:09.781 --> 08:11.241
We don't want to leave
anything behind.

08:11.325 --> 08:12.492
Go flush this.

08:12.576 --> 08:15.204
You know, after I get my money,

08:15.287 --> 08:17.247
I may have some of my guys go by

08:17.331 --> 08:19.208
and find Neagley's father,
pick him up.

08:19.291 --> 08:20.626
That ought to flush her
out of the woodwork.

08:20.709 --> 08:21.835
What do you think?

08:21.919 --> 08:23.670
I just really,
really hate loose ends.

08:27.007 --> 08:29.009
♪ ♪

08:32.429 --> 08:35.015
[♪ Jefferson Airplane:
"White Rabbit"]

08:35.098 --> 08:38.352
♪ One pill makes you larger ♪

08:38.435 --> 08:41.980
♪ And one pill
makes you small... ♪

08:42.064 --> 08:43.523
Are those fucking kids back?

08:45.317 --> 08:46.902
Go run them the hell
out of here.

08:46.985 --> 08:48.904
We don't want any witnesses
when we leave.

08:50.364 --> 08:53.116
♪ Go ask Alice ♪

08:54.451 --> 08:57.621
♪ When she's ten feet tall ♪

08:59.206 --> 09:03.752
♪ And if you go
chasing rabbits ♪

09:03.835 --> 09:08.632
♪ And you know
you're going to fall... ♪

09:09.675 --> 09:13.804
Hey! I thought I told you kids
to stay the hell away from here.

09:13.887 --> 09:18.225
♪ Has given you the call ♪

09:18.308 --> 09:19.559
♪ Call Alice ♪

09:19.643 --> 09:21.436
[door buzzes]

09:21.520 --> 09:22.854
♪ When she was just small... ♪

09:22.938 --> 09:24.064
I'm telling you
for the last time,

09:24.147 --> 09:25.357
get back in your car,

09:25.440 --> 09:27.818
get out of here
before I kick your ass.

09:27.901 --> 09:30.862
Okay, boss. Just let me
finish my beer, okay?

09:31.863 --> 09:36.285
♪ Have fallen sloppy dead ♪

09:36.368 --> 09:38.287
♪ And the White Knight... ♪

09:38.370 --> 09:40.622
As soon as you have them
secure on that 'copter,

09:40.706 --> 09:43.333
go find out why that
fucking music is still playing.

09:43.417 --> 09:46.003
♪ Off with her head ♪

09:46.044 --> 09:52.259
♪ Remember what
the Dormouse said... ♪

09:53.719 --> 09:56.013
[powering up]

09:56.096 --> 09:58.473
- What the fuck is going on?
- ♪ Feed your head ♪

09:58.557 --> 09:59.391
[Pierce] Now!

09:59.474 --> 10:03.395
♪ Feed your head ♪

10:03.437 --> 10:07.566
♪ Feed your head ♪♪

10:07.607 --> 10:09.443
Ah!

10:09.484 --> 10:11.153
[gunfire]

10:17.159 --> 10:18.160
[man grunts]

10:29.629 --> 10:31.173
[grunting]

10:36.678 --> 10:37.888
[groans]

10:46.313 --> 10:48.732
[Lennox] Hey, hey!

10:48.815 --> 10:50.942
Keep your head down
and stay here.

10:51.026 --> 10:51.943
Come on!

10:52.027 --> 10:53.737
- Over there.
- Stay here.

10:57.657 --> 10:58.575
[grunts]

11:13.507 --> 11:15.300
♪ ♪

11:23.016 --> 11:24.726
- [panting] Hey, boss.
- Neagley.

11:24.810 --> 11:28.772
We got to cut our losses,
meet our buyer, get paid,

11:28.855 --> 11:30.232
get the hell out of the country

11:30.315 --> 11:32.317
before the cops
and the feds show up.

11:34.152 --> 11:35.278
Jefferson Airplane?

11:35.362 --> 11:36.530
Why no Hendrix?

11:36.613 --> 11:39.032
I'm with Swan.
Hendrix is overrated.

11:41.118 --> 11:43.495
- [Parker] What about
the other guys?
- Fuck 'em!

11:51.878 --> 11:52.838
Ah!

11:57.342 --> 11:58.760
Langston's getting away.

12:05.308 --> 12:06.726
Get this thing up in the air.

12:06.810 --> 12:09.062
It's gonna take a few minutes
to warm up first.

12:09.146 --> 12:11.440
No. Let's go now,
you son of a bitch.

12:11.523 --> 12:12.524
All right.

12:15.986 --> 12:17.279
How much ammo you got?

12:17.362 --> 12:18.822
Not enough to cover
your slow ass

12:18.905 --> 12:20.157
if you're planning on
running out of here.

12:20.240 --> 12:21.366
You're gonna have to make do.

12:21.450 --> 12:22.451
On three.

12:22.534 --> 12:25.912
One, two, three.

12:41.678 --> 12:42.929
[Langston] Here we go.

12:53.690 --> 12:54.900
Shit.

13:00.780 --> 13:02.782
[grunting, panting]

13:09.998 --> 13:11.708
Open the back doors.

13:21.801 --> 13:23.220
Ladies first.

13:23.303 --> 13:25.805
It's your turn, sweetheart.

13:28.391 --> 13:30.560
Time for you to fly.

13:34.064 --> 13:35.690
Fuck. [grunts]

13:35.774 --> 13:36.900
- Fuck!
- [yells]

13:36.983 --> 13:38.401
[grunts]

13:38.485 --> 13:39.986
[grunting]

13:43.698 --> 13:44.783
Ah!

13:46.618 --> 13:47.869
- [grunts]
- [shouts]

13:57.921 --> 14:00.799
Fuck it. Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

14:01.675 --> 14:03.260
[both grunting]

14:03.343 --> 14:04.678
[gasps]

14:04.761 --> 14:05.720
Reacher!

14:05.804 --> 14:06.888
- [yelps]
- [grunts]

14:10.559 --> 14:12.561
[alarm beeping]

14:15.480 --> 14:17.691
[both grunting]

14:24.406 --> 14:26.241
[screaming]

14:26.324 --> 14:27.742
[gasps]

14:40.297 --> 14:42.132
Jesus Christ, Reacher.

14:42.215 --> 14:43.675
You just don't know

14:43.758 --> 14:44.968
- when to quit!
- [grunts]

14:45.051 --> 14:46.094
[grunting]

14:48.680 --> 14:49.598
[grunts]

14:50.765 --> 14:51.725
Ah!

14:57.314 --> 14:59.983
You're one tough son of a bitch,
I'll give you that.

15:03.403 --> 15:04.696
Get him.

15:08.867 --> 15:10.035
[Parker] Here's the deal.

15:10.118 --> 15:13.079
I can use
your pal's brass knuckles

15:13.163 --> 15:16.499
and smash your skull, or...

15:16.583 --> 15:18.043
you can let the bitch fall,

15:18.126 --> 15:21.838
and I'll be merciful
and toss you out after her.

15:21.921 --> 15:25.008
[shouts indistinctly]

15:26.593 --> 15:28.845
- [Dixon shouts]
- Ah!

15:28.887 --> 15:30.513
[panting]

15:40.023 --> 15:41.232
[Langston] No, no.

15:42.984 --> 15:44.194
Wait...

15:48.907 --> 15:50.283
You better hold
this thing steady,

15:50.367 --> 15:52.911
or we're gonna find out
the hard way if I can land it.

15:52.994 --> 15:54.120
Yes, ma'am.

15:54.204 --> 15:55.288
Wait, wait, wait.

15:55.372 --> 15:56.581
Wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait...

15:56.665 --> 15:57.624
Oh!

15:59.959 --> 16:01.670
No, no, no, no! You...

16:01.753 --> 16:03.296
You can still
stop the missiles

16:03.380 --> 16:05.423
from getting into
the hands of the terrorists.

16:05.507 --> 16:06.966
No, no, no, no!
No, no, no!

16:07.050 --> 16:08.426
Don't! Don't kill me,
and I'll tell you

16:08.510 --> 16:10.136
where I was gonna meet Mahmoud.

16:10.220 --> 16:12.847
You assume that's the
information I need, Langston.

16:14.140 --> 16:17.644
But in an investigation,
assumptions kill.

16:17.727 --> 16:18.645
No.

16:19.813 --> 16:21.189
[shouts]

16:25.026 --> 16:26.486
[grunts]

16:28.446 --> 16:30.782
[O'Donnell] That was
a really cool line,

16:30.865 --> 16:33.868
but I hope you actually know
where the hell A.M.'s heading.

16:33.952 --> 16:36.913
I don't. But he does.

16:36.996 --> 16:38.873
What do you say, flyboy?

16:38.957 --> 16:40.792
They're going to meet
one of the New Age engineers

16:40.875 --> 16:42.419
at his home
so he can teach the buyers

16:42.502 --> 16:45.088
how to put the Little Wing chips
into the rockets.

16:45.171 --> 16:47.841
Look, I have the coordinates.
Please, just don't kill me.

16:49.008 --> 16:50.844
Take us there.

16:55.724 --> 16:57.726
[whirring fades]

17:04.649 --> 17:06.651
♪ ♪

17:19.456 --> 17:21.249
[brakes squeal]

17:21.332 --> 17:22.792
[engine stops]

17:22.876 --> 17:24.419
[door opens]

17:26.713 --> 17:28.715
[wind whistling]

17:33.386 --> 17:35.972
[A.M.] Excellent.
Langston's already here.

17:50.737 --> 17:52.363
[muffled gunshot]

17:59.829 --> 18:00.872
You're not Langston.

18:02.373 --> 18:04.292
No shit.

18:06.961 --> 18:08.213
Get inside.

18:18.056 --> 18:19.307
There must be some mistake.

18:19.390 --> 18:21.392
I don't know any of you people.

18:21.476 --> 18:22.936
Sorry to disappoint.

18:23.019 --> 18:24.687
Your little scientist friend's
being held in the barn

18:24.771 --> 18:25.939
with the pilot.

18:27.774 --> 18:29.776
You killed our friends.

18:33.279 --> 18:35.281
Over this stuff.

18:39.911 --> 18:41.079
You killed them.

18:41.162 --> 18:42.831
[stammers] I understand
that you're upset,

18:42.914 --> 18:44.374
but I didn't kill your friends.

18:44.457 --> 18:46.668
- I didn't even know them.
- [Reacher] But I know you.

18:46.751 --> 18:48.503
You don't care
how many people die

18:48.586 --> 18:49.921
so long as you get
your finder's fee.

18:50.004 --> 18:53.216
Arrest me and get it over with.

18:53.299 --> 18:56.636
We could do that, but...

18:56.719 --> 18:58.429
bet a guy like you...

19:00.265 --> 19:04.018
...probably got a top-notch
lawyer on speed dial.

19:04.102 --> 19:05.895
We'll give you one chance.

19:05.979 --> 19:07.647
Tell us who you're
selling the weapons to.

19:07.730 --> 19:11.526
Oh, I-I'm sorry, that would ruin
my reputation and my business.

19:11.609 --> 19:13.862
Not that I would expect
any of you to understand.

19:13.945 --> 19:15.488
I can see that you're idealists.

19:15.572 --> 19:18.366
Besides, your issues
aren't with me.

19:18.449 --> 19:20.118
I don't fire the weapons.
I'm the middleman.

19:20.201 --> 19:21.786
It's-it's just business.

19:21.870 --> 19:24.455
- You think
that makes it better?
- [A.M.] Yes, I do.

19:24.539 --> 19:26.708
Between the seller of
the gun or the user,

19:26.791 --> 19:28.293
I prefer to be the seller.

19:28.376 --> 19:30.753
The base mindset that
a person has to embrace

19:30.837 --> 19:32.422
to actually pull the trigger
is no better than...

19:32.505 --> 19:34.173
- [gunshot]
- [grunts]

19:34.257 --> 19:35.341
[scoffs]

19:35.425 --> 19:37.427
[breathing heavily]

20:02.702 --> 20:05.163
♪ ♪

20:05.204 --> 20:06.748
[door opens]

20:13.046 --> 20:14.380
Here.

20:27.226 --> 20:29.395
[Seaver] Guessing
from all the gunfire

20:29.479 --> 20:31.856
we don't have anyone
to worry about anymore.

20:31.940 --> 20:34.192
- [Reacher] Affirmative.
- [Seaver] Huh.

20:34.275 --> 20:36.110
What do you want to do
with these two?

20:36.194 --> 20:38.196
[pilot breathes heavily]

20:41.658 --> 20:42.825
Hey, man.

20:42.909 --> 20:44.369
I didn't kill anyone,

20:44.452 --> 20:46.079
and I didn't have anything
to do with those missiles.

20:46.162 --> 20:47.872
I only flew the chopper.

20:47.956 --> 20:49.123
I was just doing my job.

20:49.207 --> 20:50.959
What's your excuse?

20:51.042 --> 20:53.294
I was just gonna show him
how to implement the chips.

20:53.378 --> 20:56.172
I had no idea what they were all
gonna be used for.

20:56.255 --> 20:58.758
Please, I'm just an engineer.

21:03.596 --> 21:05.807
Get out of here.
Both of you.

21:05.848 --> 21:07.600
- Thanks.
- Thanks.

21:21.781 --> 21:23.783
[helicopter whirring softly]

21:33.710 --> 21:35.712
[whirring increases]

21:37.755 --> 21:39.674
Don't hog the beer, O'Donnell.

21:39.757 --> 21:40.967
Yeah.

21:50.143 --> 21:52.353
Cold tonight.

21:52.437 --> 21:54.272
Only gonna get colder.

21:54.355 --> 21:55.565
Yup.

21:57.942 --> 22:00.445
Just wait till
they're over the river,

22:00.528 --> 22:01.904
past that ridge.

22:01.988 --> 22:03.406
Copy that.

22:07.618 --> 22:09.787
[O'Donnell coughs, mutters]

22:15.543 --> 22:16.753
I think we're good, Neagley.

22:16.836 --> 22:18.296
Fire in the hole.

22:26.137 --> 22:28.181
Wait for it...

22:35.938 --> 22:37.982
I guess Little Wing works.

22:40.193 --> 22:42.195
[rifles click]

22:43.404 --> 22:45.406
You got to be shitting me.

22:45.490 --> 22:47.533
Sorry, but Senator Lavoy
was clear.

22:47.617 --> 22:49.577
No one can ever know
what really happened.

22:49.660 --> 22:51.662
Can't take the risk
one of you might talk.

22:51.746 --> 22:53.164
I underestimated you guys.

22:53.247 --> 22:54.749
Didn't think
we'd take it this far?

22:54.832 --> 22:56.167
[Reacher] Didn't think
you'd wait this long.

22:56.250 --> 22:57.418
I thought you might make a move

22:57.502 --> 22:58.669
as soon as I let them
get on the chopper.

22:58.753 --> 23:00.004
Me, too.

23:00.088 --> 23:01.214
Maybe they just really wanted

23:01.297 --> 23:02.632
to see me shoot
those assholes down.

23:02.715 --> 23:03.966
It was pretty cool.

23:04.050 --> 23:06.344
[Reacher] I figured Lavoy was
the kind of guy

23:06.427 --> 23:07.595
that would cover his ass.

23:07.678 --> 23:09.639
That's why I didn't just
call Lavoy.

23:09.722 --> 23:11.849
I also called Omar Karim
in Homeland.

23:11.933 --> 23:13.434
[siren chirping]

23:13.518 --> 23:15.061
I think that's him now.

23:15.144 --> 23:17.897
♪ ♪

23:19.565 --> 23:20.983
[tac team leader] Down,
down, down!

23:21.067 --> 23:22.193
[tac squad member] Hands!

23:22.276 --> 23:23.653
- Let me see your hands!
- Move!

23:23.736 --> 23:24.946
Cutting it pretty close.

23:25.029 --> 23:26.656
When is government
ever efficient?

23:28.282 --> 23:30.701
- Lavoy?
- Tac team's standing by.

23:30.785 --> 23:33.412
Thought you might want
to do the honors.

23:43.089 --> 23:44.048
[line ringing]

23:44.132 --> 23:46.134
[ringing]

23:49.720 --> 23:50.930
Is it over?

23:51.013 --> 23:52.473
[Reacher over phone] Almost.

23:52.557 --> 23:55.518
There's just one last loose end
that needs tying up.

23:55.601 --> 23:57.645
I think this is
what's called a win-win.

24:00.940 --> 24:02.150
You've got the green light.

24:02.233 --> 24:04.110
[tac team member] Lavoy!
Homeland Security!

24:04.193 --> 24:06.112
Lay on the ground!
Get down!

24:06.195 --> 24:08.114
Show me your hands.

24:08.197 --> 24:09.365
Move, move, move!

24:09.448 --> 24:10.408
[disconnect tone]

24:10.491 --> 24:12.285
Lavoy's having a bad day.

24:12.368 --> 24:13.494
We had a deal.

24:13.578 --> 24:15.329
Get going.
We'll clean up here.

24:19.333 --> 24:21.752
Oh, one more thing...

24:21.836 --> 24:22.879
Where's the money?

24:24.964 --> 24:26.382
What money?

24:28.092 --> 24:31.095
[♪ The Crutch: "Keep On Risin'"]

24:32.388 --> 24:34.265
♪ Whoo ♪

24:40.855 --> 24:43.316
♪ I'm on my way ♪

24:43.399 --> 24:45.776
♪ Got the light of day ♪

24:45.860 --> 24:47.695
♪ Living on parade ♪

24:47.778 --> 24:48.738
♪ Yeah ♪

24:48.821 --> 24:50.907
♪ Making history, yeah ♪

24:50.948 --> 24:53.409
♪ Passing county lines ♪

24:53.492 --> 24:55.912
♪ Racking up the miles ♪

24:55.995 --> 24:58.539
♪ Flying by the signs, whoa ♪

25:00.750 --> 25:04.879
♪ And I keep on keeping on ♪

25:06.255 --> 25:08.257
♪ I'll keep on rising... ♪

25:11.219 --> 25:13.638
[all grunt softly]

25:13.721 --> 25:14.931
Looks like you had
a rough night.

25:15.014 --> 25:16.891
Had worse.

25:16.974 --> 25:18.392
[waitress] What can I get you?

25:18.476 --> 25:20.561
Coffee. Black.

25:20.645 --> 25:21.687
Same.

25:21.771 --> 25:23.189
Yeah, you can bring the pot.

25:23.272 --> 25:24.982
For you, ma'am?

25:25.066 --> 25:26.067
Cereal.

25:26.150 --> 25:27.276
Pops, Puffs or Pebbles,

25:27.360 --> 25:29.070
in that order of preference.

25:29.153 --> 25:30.613
And a chocolate milkshake,
thanks.

25:38.079 --> 25:39.914
So...

25:39.997 --> 25:42.500
what are we gonna do
with 65 million simoleons?

25:42.583 --> 25:44.585
That's a lot of lettuce.

25:44.669 --> 25:47.546
Got to use it to make up for
some of the pain it caused.

25:47.630 --> 25:51.300
Sure, but what specifically?

25:51.384 --> 25:52.802
Big decisions...

25:52.885 --> 25:55.721
Well, I sure am glad
that I'm not the senior officer

25:55.805 --> 25:58.599
in charge of this unit,
got to make choices like that.

25:58.683 --> 26:00.268
Don't look at me.

26:00.351 --> 26:01.894
[chuckling] What a shocker.

26:01.978 --> 26:04.814
The guy with no mortgage,
no car payments and no job

26:04.897 --> 26:06.816
- doesn't want
the responsibility.
- [Dixon] You care less

26:06.899 --> 26:09.568
about money than anybody
I've ever met, Reacher.

26:09.652 --> 26:12.488
You should be in charge of it.
Handle it, Big Guy.

26:14.532 --> 26:16.784
- Thank you.
- [TV announcer] This just in...

26:16.867 --> 26:18.995
[news anchor] Police say
they've recovered two bodies

26:19.078 --> 26:20.621
from the wreckage of
a helicopter that went down

26:20.705 --> 26:23.291
in the Hudson River
early this morning.

26:23.374 --> 26:24.875
- Just terrible.
- [news anchor] A fisherman
who witnessed the crash...

26:24.959 --> 26:26.544
Yeah. Real shame.

26:26.627 --> 26:28.004
[news anchor] ...said the
chopper had a stream of smoke

26:28.087 --> 26:31.173
trailing behind it,
followed by an explosion.

26:31.257 --> 26:33.592
Investigators are
blaming the tragedy

26:33.676 --> 26:36.637
on system malfunction
and possibly pilot error.

26:36.721 --> 26:39.390
Sounds like your friend
at Homeland has things handled.

26:41.142 --> 26:42.310
Got 50 cents?

26:42.393 --> 26:45.271
You have 65 million
three inches from you.

26:45.354 --> 26:47.440
Juke boxes don't take
bearer bonds.

26:57.116 --> 26:58.993
Start me a new tab.

27:00.077 --> 27:01.454
[Neagley] Mm-hmm.

27:01.537 --> 27:03.748
[new anchor continues
indistinctly]

27:14.633 --> 27:17.803
[♪ Quaker City Night Hawks:
"Beat the Machine"]

27:22.850 --> 27:26.520
♪ Took down my coat
and I put it on ♪

27:26.604 --> 27:29.357
♪ Put cold hands
through the sleeves ♪

27:30.608 --> 27:34.320
♪ Pulled down my hat
and I rode along ♪

27:34.403 --> 27:37.156
♪ Silent ice in the trees ♪

27:38.366 --> 27:41.702
♪ I rode right past
all the soldiers there ♪

27:41.786 --> 27:44.830
♪ Got in the bridge
cross the creek ♪

27:46.082 --> 27:47.583
♪ The lonesome sounds... ♪

27:47.666 --> 27:49.251
[Russo] How can you not know
where it came from?

27:49.335 --> 27:51.087
You're the bank.
Yeah.

27:51.170 --> 27:53.464
It's millions of dollars
earmarked for my kids.

27:55.174 --> 27:56.634
It can't be from my brother.

27:56.717 --> 27:57.927
He...

27:58.969 --> 28:01.305
...he died recently.

28:01.347 --> 28:03.015
♪ Oh... ♪

28:03.099 --> 28:05.059
I'm gonna miss you.

28:05.142 --> 28:06.560
Take care of the spot.

28:06.644 --> 28:08.562
We got you.
Send us a postcard.

28:08.646 --> 28:10.689
[laughing] Key West or bust.

28:10.773 --> 28:13.109
♪ Rode three days
through the howling rain ♪

28:13.192 --> 28:15.986
♪ Towards the kingdoms
in the East ♪

28:17.446 --> 28:20.616
♪ And I heard that
great dog of winter there ♪

28:20.699 --> 28:23.452
♪ Call through
the darkness to me ♪

28:25.204 --> 28:28.666
♪ He asked how long
till the war come to him ♪

28:28.749 --> 28:31.210
♪ I said not till the spring ♪

28:31.293 --> 28:32.962
[crying]

28:33.045 --> 28:35.423
♪ Oh ♪

28:36.465 --> 28:38.717
[man] Hey, do we know
someone named Swan?

28:38.801 --> 28:40.553
Or a dog named Maisi?

28:40.636 --> 28:42.221
I don't think so. Why?

28:44.932 --> 28:46.934
Got a donation in their name.

28:47.810 --> 28:51.480
♪ Oh, oh ♪

28:52.606 --> 28:55.484
♪ You can't get what you need ♪

28:55.568 --> 28:59.155
♪ Oh, oh ♪

28:59.238 --> 29:03.159
Mr. Neagley, I'm Connie Bumbry
from Chicago Home Health.

29:03.242 --> 29:05.077
I'm part of the team
that's been hired

29:05.161 --> 29:07.163
to provide you
around-the-clock medical care.

29:11.333 --> 29:12.751
[phone clicks]

29:14.753 --> 29:16.338
[Neagley] That was my dad.

29:17.840 --> 29:19.550
What did you do?

29:19.633 --> 29:20.759
You would've felt funny

29:20.843 --> 29:22.803
if I'd just put cash
in your account,

29:22.887 --> 29:24.430
but you won't take it away
from your father.

29:24.513 --> 29:27.391
He's good for
the rest of his life.

29:27.475 --> 29:29.310
Whatever he needs.

29:29.393 --> 29:31.395
There's more than a bit
left over for you.

29:35.858 --> 29:37.860
I ever tell you
you're a good friend, Reacher?

29:39.778 --> 29:41.363
Not nearly enough.

29:47.036 --> 29:49.246
What about me?

29:49.330 --> 29:51.290
What did the world's
scariest Santa Claus

29:51.373 --> 29:52.875
put under my tree this year?

29:52.958 --> 29:54.627
I didn't give you a penny.

29:54.710 --> 29:57.046
but I put a shitload
in your kids' names.

29:57.129 --> 30:00.716
Credit Union around the corner
from your house.

30:00.799 --> 30:04.553
It'll cover private school
tuition, college, trade school.

30:04.637 --> 30:05.679
From the looks of it,

30:05.763 --> 30:07.014
the defense lawyers
they'll eventually need.

30:07.097 --> 30:09.517
[laughs]

30:09.600 --> 30:11.018
Now you only have
to take the sleazy,

30:11.101 --> 30:12.686
adjacent jobs you want to take.

30:15.898 --> 30:17.816
I'm, uh, speechless.

30:17.900 --> 30:19.693
That's a first.

30:19.777 --> 30:21.570
[laughs]

30:21.654 --> 30:24.532
Speaking of jobs...
you can quit yours.

30:24.615 --> 30:26.784
I started
a Delaware LLC in your name.

30:26.867 --> 30:29.328
Fully funded.
Go hang your own shingle.

30:29.411 --> 30:31.705
You're too smart to be
working for anyone but yourself.

30:31.789 --> 30:33.916
[laughs]

30:33.999 --> 30:37.211
Wow. I, uh...
I just, um...

30:39.713 --> 30:41.674
Wow.

30:41.757 --> 30:43.133
Thank you.

30:46.262 --> 30:48.556
What about you, Big Dog?

30:48.639 --> 30:50.224
What did you get for yourself?

30:52.893 --> 30:54.436
I need a new toothbrush.

30:54.520 --> 30:56.522
[chuckles]

31:01.360 --> 31:02.820
Oh, my God, he's serious.

31:07.449 --> 31:08.784
You know, Reacher,

31:08.867 --> 31:10.744
when I found out that
you were... [sniffles]

31:10.828 --> 31:12.329
...wandering the Earth

31:12.413 --> 31:15.416
with nothing but what you could
carry in your pockets...

31:15.499 --> 31:17.126
I thought you'd lost your mind.

31:18.252 --> 31:19.712
But...

31:19.795 --> 31:22.214
there's a part of me
that thinks that

31:22.298 --> 31:24.592
you're the only one out of us
that's got it all figured out.

31:29.888 --> 31:31.307
Can't believe
I'm gonna say this,

31:31.390 --> 31:35.311
but I actually miss Swan's
guitar playing right now.

31:40.608 --> 31:42.276
To absent friends.

31:42.359 --> 31:44.778
- To absent friends.
- To absent friends.

31:49.074 --> 31:50.367
[exhales sharply]

31:50.451 --> 31:52.036
[clears throat] So...

31:53.912 --> 31:55.539
...this is it.

31:57.291 --> 31:58.917
It's our last night together.

32:05.215 --> 32:07.051
We should take another picture.

32:07.134 --> 32:08.302
Yeah, we should.

32:08.385 --> 32:10.054
Hell yeah.

32:10.137 --> 32:12.014
Guess you're not gonna let me
just take this one either, huh?

32:12.097 --> 32:13.223
Not a chance, boss.

32:13.307 --> 32:14.475
Hey. Come on.

32:16.268 --> 32:17.811
[Dixon sighs]

32:17.895 --> 32:19.605
Okay.

32:19.688 --> 32:21.690
[beeping]

32:30.574 --> 32:32.576
♪ ♪

32:50.928 --> 32:52.638
Good, you're awake.

32:54.473 --> 32:56.308
I thought you'd gone.

32:56.392 --> 32:59.019
I did.

32:59.103 --> 33:01.271
Bought you a present.

33:05.109 --> 33:06.235
[grunts softly]

33:06.318 --> 33:07.903
[sniffles]

33:08.904 --> 33:10.406
Now you can actually
get yourself something

33:10.489 --> 33:11.699
with the money.

33:13.742 --> 33:15.119
Please, Reacher.

33:15.202 --> 33:17.246
You deserve it.
Do it for me.

33:19.248 --> 33:20.207
Okay.

33:23.085 --> 33:24.753
And there's something
else you can do.

33:24.837 --> 33:25.754
Name it.

33:25.838 --> 33:27.798
Come home with me.

33:27.881 --> 33:29.800
I really want you
to meet my parents.

33:34.263 --> 33:35.597
I'm fucking with you.

33:35.681 --> 33:37.182
[inhales, sighs]

33:37.266 --> 33:38.434
[Dixon laughs]

33:38.517 --> 33:41.228
Look, I don't know about you,

33:41.311 --> 33:44.565
but I see what we've been
doing these past few days

33:44.648 --> 33:47.985
not so much as...

33:48.068 --> 33:52.281
"new business"
but "old business."

33:56.952 --> 33:59.246
Old business that really needed
to be taken care of.

33:59.329 --> 34:00.247
[Dixon] Mm.

34:00.330 --> 34:02.708
Damn right it did.

34:02.791 --> 34:06.754
And before this
meeting's adjourned,

34:06.837 --> 34:10.924
I think this particular item
needs one last going over.

34:12.050 --> 34:13.719
I second that motion,

34:13.802 --> 34:16.305
but I saw O'Donnell out front,

34:16.388 --> 34:17.931
and I told him that
I'd share a cab with him

34:18.015 --> 34:20.392
to the airport
so I've only got a minute.

34:21.685 --> 34:23.520
This might take
more than a minute.

34:25.439 --> 34:27.232
That's not what O'Donnell said.

34:27.316 --> 34:30.736
[♪ Lynyrd Skynyrd: "Simple Man"]

34:35.407 --> 34:36.992
♪ Mama told me ♪

34:37.075 --> 34:38.744
[Neagley] This is what
you bought yourself?

34:38.827 --> 34:40.704
- A bus pass?
- ♪ When I was young... ♪

34:40.788 --> 34:42.456
That's a Trailways Pass.

34:42.539 --> 34:45.667
I can ride the bus anywhere
in the country for a year.

34:45.751 --> 34:48.962
That's $1,980 of freedom,
Neagley.

34:49.046 --> 34:51.465
[Neagley] Well, I guess
at least for the next 365 days

34:51.548 --> 34:53.091
I won't have to worry
that you're out there

34:53.175 --> 34:54.718
hopping freight trains.

34:56.303 --> 34:58.013
And, for the record...

35:00.432 --> 35:01.934
...I'm not as comfortable
with this arrangement

35:02.017 --> 35:03.185
as I thought I was.

35:03.268 --> 35:06.146
Years without seeing each other,
never speaking,

35:06.230 --> 35:08.816
getting together
only when we're being shot at?

35:10.442 --> 35:12.653
You need to get better
at staying in touch.

35:14.613 --> 35:15.739
Is that understood?

35:15.823 --> 35:18.116
Yes, Master Sergeant.

35:23.831 --> 35:26.375
♪ Oh, take your time ♪

35:27.459 --> 35:30.295
♪ Don't live too fast... ♪

35:32.130 --> 35:33.549
Bye, Neagley.

35:36.051 --> 35:38.679
♪ And they will pass... ♪

35:38.762 --> 35:40.681
[Neagley] One more thing.

35:40.764 --> 35:44.142
You've referred to the Special
Investigators as your team,

35:44.226 --> 35:46.979
your soldiers,
even your friends.

35:49.022 --> 35:51.066
But you know
we're more than that, right?

35:51.149 --> 35:55.863
♪ There's someone up above ♪

35:55.946 --> 36:03.370
♪ And be a simple kind of man ♪

36:03.453 --> 36:07.124
♪ Oh, be something ♪

36:07.207 --> 36:10.878
♪ You love and understand ♪

36:10.961 --> 36:15.465
♪ Baby, be a simple ♪

36:15.549 --> 36:19.386
♪ Kind of man ♪

36:19.469 --> 36:23.390
♪ Oh, won't you do this
for me, son ♪

36:23.473 --> 36:25.767
♪ If you can? ♪

36:29.646 --> 36:31.481
Where you coming from?

36:32.691 --> 36:33.817
Right here.

36:33.901 --> 36:35.152
Doing what?

36:35.235 --> 36:38.113
♪ Forget your lust ♪

36:38.196 --> 36:39.615
Visiting family.

36:39.698 --> 36:41.867
♪ For the rich man's gold ♪

36:41.950 --> 36:43.201
So, where you headed?

36:43.285 --> 36:46.330
♪ All that you need ♪

36:46.413 --> 36:47.706
No idea.

36:47.789 --> 36:49.791
♪ Is in your soul ♪

36:51.877 --> 36:58.175
♪ And be a simple kind of man ♪

36:59.176 --> 37:02.930
♪ Oh, be something ♪

37:03.013 --> 37:07.142
♪ You love and understand ♪

37:07.225 --> 37:14.483
♪ Baby, be a simple
kind of man ♪

37:15.484 --> 37:19.112
♪ Oh, won't you do this
for me, son ♪

37:19.196 --> 37:21.740
♪ If you can? ♪

37:21.823 --> 37:23.742
♪ Oh, yes, I will ♪

37:23.825 --> 37:25.827
♪ ♪

37:53.855 --> 37:55.857
♪ ♪

38:16.837 --> 38:18.505
♪ Boy, don't you worry ♪

38:20.382 --> 38:22.968
♪ You'll find yourself ♪

38:24.594 --> 38:26.513
♪ Follow your heart ♪

38:28.557 --> 38:31.143
♪ And nothing else ♪

38:32.769 --> 38:34.688
♪ And you can do this ♪

38:34.771 --> 38:38.608
♪ Oh, baby, if you try ♪

38:40.068 --> 38:44.114
♪ All that I want
for you, my son ♪

38:44.197 --> 38:47.993
♪ Is to be satisfied ♪

38:48.076 --> 38:51.913
♪ And be a simple ♪

38:51.997 --> 38:56.043
♪ Kind of man ♪

38:56.126 --> 38:59.212
♪ Oh, be something ♪

38:59.296 --> 39:03.216
♪ You love and understand ♪

39:03.258 --> 39:07.471
♪ Baby, be a simple ♪

39:07.554 --> 39:09.890
♪ Kind of man ♪♪
